n some people look over the character sheet for Ignatia Firesong? She's a character of mine in a manga I'm working on. Right now, the profile I have for her seems kind of...dull. (if you want to see a pic, find the post called &quot;ahh...a decent cg after so many failures&quot; or something like that under the color art forum)<br>
<br>
Ignatia Firesong: <br>
Age: 19<br>
<br>
DOB: September 22, 1986<br>
<br>
Codename: Hwo (chinese for Fire)<br>
<br>
Nicknames: Katt, Iggi-chan, Tia.<br>
<br>
Occupation: College Student, Professional Manga Artist for Paranoia, Former agent for the Chinese Sector of the Defense Base of Terren (name of the world they live on) <br>
<br>
Blood Type: ? (I'm trying to find the explanation the Japanese people have for the personality of the blood types, so far, I have only found the explanation for &quot;b&quot;. If anyone has some information, please please please send it to me!)<br>
<br>
Height: 154 cm (about 5'1&quot;)<br>
<br>
Weight: 108 lbs (49 kg)<br>
<br>
Hair color: Brown with two red streaks in the bangs and one long streak down the side.<br>
<br>
Eye color: green<br>
<br>
Skin tone: tanned<br>
<br>
Weapons: Straight sword, Brass knuckles, tiger claws, and metal fan.<br>
<br>
Favorite People: Kokoro, Bradley Trinn, Ajina, Opal, Erin, Shway, Di, and Fon<br>
<br>
Least Favorite people: Mizu, Chi, Hi and Kaze (four elementals of Japanese sector), Professor Zander (Physics teacher)<br>
<br>
Habits: staying up till three in the morning drawing, spending hours at a time in front of the computer, starting too many projects and not finishing any.<br>
<br>
Hobbies: beating the crap out of a punching bag, drawing, reading, surfing the net, defending the world..<br>
<br>
Personality: assertive and confident, Ignatia shares the job of the main graphic artist with Trinn for the group &quot;paranoia.&quot; As a virgo and a tiger, she has a habit of expecting too much of someone and being a perfectionist 24/7. Her elemental sign is of fire, despite the fact that virgo is an earth sign. Being a fire, she can be somewhat temperatmental and loud when irritated, not to mention too stubborn for her own good. When she doesn't like something, she lets people know her opinion.<br>
<br>
Clothing: Being very physical and active, Ignatia plays a lot of different sports at the College. She's the only one of Paranoia who regularly attends health seminars and sports clubs, depending on the season and her mood. Most of her wardrobe consists of shorts and comfortable tanktops for the summer; long sleeve shirts, soccer shirts and baggy pants of any material for the winder. Her footwear is mainly the lavender and gray sneakers and her trademark black combat boots. Occasionally, she'll put on a pair of white or black strappy sandals. Comfort is preferred rather then style (pants to skirt ratio: 6:1).<br>
<br>
Speaking Manner: Ignatia knows two languages fluently and is learning her third and fourth at the college. After being on the sports field for years with crude guys, she has picked up some slang. Most of the time, her speaking is rather proper and polite. When irritated, he slang comes out (ie: &quot;I will not tolerate this any longer&quot;-&gt;&quot;I ain't gonna take this @#%$ no more!&quot;) Her speaking manner coupled by her temperamental personality has earned Ignatia a lot of enemies on and off the field. Most of the time when she's cursing, she'll slip into chinese or Japanese.<br>
<br>
